ce:section.ce:para:
Based on the plots of the PSO kinetics (Fig. 12
                           ) and the calculated kinetic parameters (Table 2
                           ) from t/qt versus time plots, there is a good agreement between experimental data and calculated q2e values for all CR concentrations. As it is observed, the K2 value increases as the CR concentration is declined, suggesting that the rate of adsorption is higher at low CR concentrations. This may be due to the fact that the adsorption of CR onto saturated active sites of N-CDs/CuFe2O4 is the rate-limiting step at higher CR concentrations. The PSO kinetic model fits the profile of the reported adsorption data, indicating that the chemisorption is the rate controlling step.
